---
// export const prerender = true;

import { siteDefaults } from '../config/siteDefaults';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageSeo = {
  title: 'Privacy Policy | nViewsWEB\'s Astro Theme',
  description: 'Learn about how we handle your data and privacy at nViewsWEB.',
  updatedDate: siteDefaults.publishedDate, // June 02 2025
};
---
<BaseLayout headProps={pageSeo} >
  <Fragment slot="headContent-top"></Fragment>
  <Fragment slot="headContent-bottom"></Fragment>
    <article class="prose mx-w-width mi-auto">
      <header class="mb-1 mx-w-content mi-auto">
        <h1 class="pb-1 ta-center">{pageSeo.title}</h1>       
      </header>       
      <div class="mx-w-content p-1 mi-auto">   
          <hr>   
            <p>Effective date: {pageSeo.updatedDate}</p>
          <p>ClampGenerator.com respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information.</p>
          <h2 id="1-information-we-collect">1. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p>We do <strong>not</strong> collect personal data like your name or email unless you submit it via the contact form. However, we collect:</p>
          <ul>
              <li><strong>Cookies</strong> for serving ads (via Google AdSense and other partners).  </li>
              <li><strong>IP address and browser information</strong> for analytics purposes (handled by Google Analytics).  </li>
              <li><strong>Contact form inputs</strong>, only when you voluntarily submit them.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We <strong>do not store this data</strong> on our servers. We rely on third-party services, which manage their own data policies.</p>
          <h2 id="2-how-we-collect-information">2. How We Collect Information</h2>
          <ul>
              <li>Through <strong>cookies</strong>, analytics, and your browser when you visit our site.  </li>
              <li>Through the <strong>contact form</strong>, where you may share your name, email, and message voluntarily.</li>
          </ul>
          <h2 id="3-third-party-services">3. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>We use the following services, each of which may collect or process data as per their policies:</p>
          <ul>
              <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> - Analytics tracking  </li>
              <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> - Ad personalization via cookies  </li>
              <li><strong>ZeptoMail &amp; AWS Mail</strong> - Sending email responses  </li>
              <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> - Performance and security  </li>
              <li><strong>GitHub</strong>  Source and deployment infrastructure</li>
          </ul>
          <h2 id="4-use-of-your-information">4. Use of Your Information</h2>
          <ul>
              <li>To process and respond to your <strong>contact form</strong> submissions.  </li>
              <li>To send occasional <strong>promotional messages</strong> (if applicable).  </li>
              <li>To improve site performance and user experience.</li>
          </ul>
          <h2 id="5-data-sharing">5. Data Sharing</h2>
          <p>We do <strong>not</strong> share or sell your data to third parties. Data is used solely for the purposes listed above.</p>
          <h2 id="6-data-storage-and-security">6. Data Storage and Security</h2>
          <p>We <strong>do not store</strong> personal user data on our servers. Third-party services like Cloudflare and Google may process information based on your browser and region.</p>
          <h2 id="7-cookies-and-tracking">7. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
          <p>We use cookies for:</p>
          <ul>
              <li>Serving relevant ads  </li>
              <li>Enhancing performance  </li>
              <li>Remembering user preferences</li>
          </ul>
          <h2 id="8-opting-out">8. Opting Out</h2>
          <p>You can control cookie settings through your browser. Refer to your browser documentation for disabling cookies or managing tracking preferences.</p>
          <h2 id="9-contact-form-submissions">9. Contact Form Submissions</h2>
          <p>When you submit a message via our contact form, we collect:</p>
          <ul>
              <li>Your <strong>name</strong> and <strong>email address</strong>  </li>
              <li>Your <strong>message content</strong>, including feedback, reviews, or questions  </li>
              <li>The <strong>selected subject</strong> (e.g., Support, Feedback, Business Inquiry)  </li>
              <li><strong>Review ratings</strong> (if submitted)  </li>
              <li><strong>Comment visibility preference</strong> (public/private)  </li>
              <li><strong>Optional metadata</strong>, such as UTM parameters (e.g., campaign, source)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We use this information solely for the purposes of responding to inquiries, collecting feedback, or reviewing suggestions. Some messages (such as reviews or public comments) may be published with user consent.</p>
          <p>We <strong>do not sell or share</strong> this information with third parties. All submissions are sent securely via email using ZeptoMail and AWS Mail, and processed by our backend (hosted on Cloudflare Workers).</p>
          <h3 id="submission-limits">Submission Limits</h3>
          <p>To prevent spam or misuse, we limit contact form submissions to once every 5 minutes. This is enforced using browser-local storage and is not linked to personal identifiers.</p>
          <h2 id="10-contact">10. Contact</h2>
          <p>For any questions or privacy concerns, contact us at:</p>
          <p>ðŸ“§ <a href="mailto:praba@nviewsweb.com"><strong>praba@nviewsweb.com</strong></a><br>ðŸ“¨ Contact Form</p>
          <h2 id="11-data-deletion">11. Data Deletion</h2>
          <p>As we do not store your personal data, there&#39;s no data to delete. However, you may request clarification via email.</p>
          <h2 id="12-children-s-privacy">12. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>ClampGenerator is intended for users <strong>13 years and older</strong>. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.</p>
  
      </div>
    </article>
  <Fragment slot="extraScripts">
  </Fragment> 
</BaseLayout>